claim.claim-text:
1. A computer for use in intracardiac ultrasound imaging, comprising:
a data connection for connecting to an ultrasound beamformer circuit; and
a processor coupled to the data connection and configured with processor-executable instructions configured to cause the processor to perform operations comprising:
storing a plurality of ultrasound image frames in memory;
storing in memory a rotational orientation of an ultrasound transducer corresponding to each of the plurality of ultrasound image frames;
detecting edges of tissue structures within each of the plurality of image frames;
determining a spatial location of each of the detected edges in each of the plurality of image frames;
statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges among a subset of the plurality of image frames with an approximately equal transducer rotational orientation to determine representative spatial locations for the tissue structures imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
generating a cartoon rendered image frame of the tissue structures based upon the representative spatial locations imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
repeating the operations of statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges and generating cartoon rendered image frames for each of a plurality of approximately equal transducer rotational orientations to generate a plurality of cartoon rendered image frames; and
combining the plurality of cartoon rendered image frames using their corresponding approximately equal transducer rotation orientations to generate a three-dimensional cartoon rendering of tissue structure.

9. A computer for use in intracardiac ultrasound imaging, comprising:
means for storing a plurality of ultrasound image frames;
means for storing a rotational orientation of an ultrasound transducer corresponding to each of the plurality of ultrasound image frames;
means for detecting edges of tissue structures within each of the plurality of image frames;
means for determining a spatial location of each of the detected edges in each of the plurality of image frames;
means for statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges among a subset of the plurality of image frames with an approximately equal transducer rotational orientation to determine representative spatial locations for the tissue structures imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
means for generating a cartoon rendered image frame of the tissue structures based upon the representative spatial locations imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
means for repeating the operations of statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges and generating cartoon rendered image frames for each of a plurality of approximately equal transducer rotational orientations to generate a plurality of cartoon rendered image frames; and
means for combining the plurality of cartoon rendered image frames using their corresponding approximately equal transducer rotation orientations to generate a three-dimensional cartoon rendering of tissue structure.

17. A method for processing a plurality of intracardiac ultrasound images stored in a computer readable memory that were obtained from an intracardiac ultrasound imaging catheter having a phased array ultrasound transducer, comprising:
receiving from the computer readable memory a plurality of ultrasound image frames and data indicating a transducer rotational orientation associated with each one of the plurality of ultrasound image frames;
detecting edges of tissue structures within each of the plurality of image frames;
determining a spatial location of each of the detected edges in each of the plurality of image frames;
statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges among a subset of the plurality of image frames with an approximately equal transducer rotational orientation to determine representative spatial locations for the tissue structures imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
generating a cartoon rendered image frame of the tissue structures based upon the representative spatial locations imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
repeating the steps of statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges and generating cartoon rendered image frames for each of a plurality of approximately equal transducer rotational orientations to generate a plurality of cartoon rendered image frames; and
combining the plurality of cartoon rendered image frames using their corresponding approximately equal transducer rotation orientations to generate a three-dimensional cartoon rendering of tissue structure.

27. A method for displaying intracardiac ultrasound images stored in a computer readable memory that were obtained from an intracardiac ultrasound imaging catheter having a phased array ultrasound transducer, comprising:
receiving from the computer readable memory a plurality of ultrasound image frames and data indicating a transducer rotational orientation associated with each one of the plurality of ultrasound image frames;
detecting edges of tissue structures within each of the plurality of image frames;
determining a spatial location of each of the detected edges in each of the plurality of image frames;
statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges among a subset of the plurality of image frames with an approximately equal transducer rotational orientation to determine representative spatial locations for the tissue structures imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
generating a cartoon rendered image frame of the tissue structures based upon the representative spatial locations imaged from the approximately equal transducer rotational orientation;
repeating the steps of statistically analyzing the spatial locations of the detected edges and generating cartoon rendered image frames for each of a plurality of approximately equal transducer rotational orientations to generate a plurality of cartoon rendered image frames;
combining the plurality of cartoon rendered image frames using their corresponding approximately equal transducer rotation orientations to generate a three-dimensional cartoon rendering of tissue structure;
presenting a graphical user interface configured to permit a user to indicate a portion of the three-dimensional cartoon rendering of tissue structure to be displayed;
receiving user inputs indicating a portion of the three-dimensional cartoon rendering of tissue structure to be displayed; and
generating a display corresponding to the user inputs.
